Chess, both Chinese and European seems to involve the idea of constantly moving ones army forward in order to take new ground, without jepeordising the
safety of that unit. Units should either remain flanked by another unit, or be in a position where the enemy cannot take that unit next turn.


1 - Process the possible moves of all pieces
2 - Eliminate any moves that would cause this piece to be taken.
(Excpt: In cases of baiting an enemy, or if it is unlikely that the play would occur because the enemy may make a greater piece more vulnerable)



AI: Create a stack by selecting the least desired moves until the top of the stack contains the most desired move and use that.


Thinking moves ahead? AI needs to calculate the moves a player may take